RESEARCH_MUNICIPALITY.notes: The City of Chicago operates under a mayor-council government system. The Mayor, City Clerk, and City Treasurer are city-wide elected officials. The City Council consists of 50 alderpersons, each representing one of the 50 wards. The list of alderpersons was compiled from multiple sources, primarily 'The Daily Line' and the City of Chicago Data Portal, which appear to be current as of late 2023/early 2024. Some names were cross-referenced with Wikipedia for full name accuracy where possible. The 4th, 5th, 6th, 14th, 21st, 26th, 30th, 34th, 44th, 46th, and 48th wards had updated alderpersons based on more recent search results.
